# tools/ = prebuilt helper mirrored from ..\STRAHLocalizationHelper\dist\ by its
# build.ps1 (117 MB self-contained exe + native dll + config.json + pdbs). It's a
# build artifact, NOT committed here — produce it by building the sibling helper repo
# (needs .NET 8 SDK). See BUILD_ENGLISH_PATCH.txt "REBUILDING THE HELPER".
tools/

# local-scripts/ = translation grunt-work + QA tooling (LLM calls, cleanup
# passes, the review/audit/sheet pipeline). NOT needed to build the patch and
# changes frequently, so kept local-only. The repo ships only the build
# scripts in scripts/. See local-scripts/requirements.txt for its deps.
local-scripts/

# issues/ is a local working area for the translation-review pipeline. None of
# it is the source of truth (apply_review_fixes.py writes fixes into texts/en/,
# and git history of texts/en/ is the authoritative change record):
#   - translation_review.xlsx : regenerable working doc / shared via OneDrive
#   - gender_audit_*.csv       : regenerable analysis reports (audit_gender.py)
#   - applied_fixes_*.csv      : per-run change logs (redundant with git diff)
issues/*.xlsx
issues/~$*
issues/gender_audit_*.csv
issues/applied_fixes_*.csv
issues/gemini_applied_*.csv
issues/anchor_align_flags.csv
issues/align_verdicts_*.csv
issues/align_boundary_flags.csv
issues/_align/
#   - subs_fuzzy_candidates.csv : anime-sub phrasing candidates (DERIVED from the
#     copyrighted anime subs via local-scripts/subs_fuzzy_poc.py; regenerable).
issues/subs_fuzzy_candidates.csv